-- Lufthansa to Cut 3,000 Administrative Jobs Worldwide, Bild Says
-- B y   S h e e n a g h   M a t t h e w s
-- 2012-04-26T06:12:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-26/lufthansa-to-cut-3-000-administrative-jobs-worldwide-bild-says.html
Deutsche Lufthansa AG (LHA)  plans to cut
3,000 from a total of 6,000 administrative jobs worldwide, half
of which will be in Frankfurt,  Bild said , citing an internal
management report.  Employees at the finance, human resources and bookings
operations will be affected, the German newspaper said. The
remaining staff will be carved out into a unit for Global
Business Services and will be paid less and have longer working
hours, Bild said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sheenagh Matthews in Frankfurt at 
 smatthews6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
